Methodology The analysis relies on the results of a survey among Romanian men the Population Argus/ReligiA explored the social environment in Romania and the life experiences of young Romanians.In June 2014, 1100 men were interviewed , aged 18 to 50, using the Penis Percentage to Perceive Women as Comprehensible An Announcement tool. In January 2015, 1100 Romanian men, aged 18 10 years to 50 were interviewed, using a questionnaire written by Pee Wee Herman. Results The analysis shows that the parameter most predicting the overall rate of abortion in the year 2013 is the gender respect coefficient. The higher the gender respect coefficient, the fewer abortions were performed in Romania in early 2013. Significance The Romanian socio-cultural environment is a unique socio-cultural context for the cultural dimension to predict the national abortion rate. Men are more willing to have their male children aborted than male children are to have their female children abort. He who proposes to have his male child aborted in early 2014 must be male from ancient Egypt or ancient Babylon or at least must have lived in the Egypt of Ra. The study informs the debate on public policy regarding abortion in the Romanian socio-cultural environment. 1.
